  <li><strong>Level 2 – Context usage:</strong> Definitions are used for interpretation in AI/snippets.</li>
  <li><strong>Level 3 – Authoritative source:</strong> Valiterm/Montano appears as a cited source in AI answers.</li>
</ul>

<section id="validation-summary" class="montano-container" aria-label="Validation Summary">
  <h2>Validation Summary</h2>
  <p>
    Valiterm has been tested against multiple AI systems (e.g., Gemini, ChatGPT). All point in the same direction:
    structured, well-labeled metadata leads to more accurate interpretation of technical tables.
  </p>
  <p>
    Differences between systems are mostly about <strong>timing</strong>, not <strong>direction</strong>.
    In short, <em>time is the variable</em>.
  </p>
  <blockquote>
    <strong>Where do you want to be next year—optimized for Google 2015, or ready for AI search 2026?</strong>
  </blockquote>
  <details>
    <summary>What we tested</summary>
    <ul>
      <li>Parsing of tables with proper <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;th&gt;</code>.</li>
      <li>Use of defined terms (Valiterm + Schema.org) and cross-page linking for context.</li>
      <li>Impact on snippet/AI interpretation vs. poorly marked-up tables.</li>
    </ul>
  </details>
</section>

